comments: Horford (BOS) moves alongside Hart's (NYK) path and incidental body contact occurs as Horford moves to a vertical position while contesting the driving shot attempt.
Williams (BOS) briefly grasps Quickley's (NYK) arm and immediately releases it as Quickley is rolling toward the rim.
Horford (BOS) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Williams (BOS) avoids initiating illegal contact with Randle (NYK) while contesting Randle's shot attempt.
Barrett (NYK) and Horford (BOS) engage and disengage in marginal contact as Horford set the pick.
Smart (BOS) shuffles his feet at the start of his dribble.
Horford (BOS) and Robinson (NYK) mutually engage and disengage as both players position themselves to rebound the ball.
Tatum (BOS) makes incidental contact with Hart's (NYK) head while shielding the ball prior to the pick. The contact is not disproportionate and is a result of a natural basketball move.
Williams' (BOS) fails to get to the height of the ball and pulls Randle's (NYK) hand off the ball during the rebound.
Brown (BOS) gets to ball height and incidental body contact occurs with Hart (NYK) as both players go for the loose ball.
Smart (BOS) commits a take foul against Quickley (NYK).
Smart (BOS) commits a take foul against Randle (NYK).
Grimes (NYK) reaches in and initiates contact with Brown's (BOS) arm which affects his ability to move into his upward shooting motion toward the rim.
Brown (NYK) dislodges the ball from Randle (NYK) any ensuing contact is incidental.
Horford (BOS) does not maintain a legal guarding position and initiates contact with Barrett's (NYK) arm during his driving shot attempt.
Barrett (NYK) momentarily rests his hand on Tatum's (BOS) side, and both players engage in marginal contact as Barrett moves around the pick.
Randle (NYK) goes to and through Smart's (BOS) body while defending the entry pass in the post.
Randle (NYK) places a collapsed forearm against Williams' (BOS) back and extends his arm which affects Williams' ability to gain possession of the loose ball.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Hart (NYK) is the last to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. The possession was correctly given to Boston.
Tatum (BOS) brings his off-arm toward Hart (NYK) and both players engage in marginal contact as Tatum is dribbling the ball on the perimeter.
Williams (BOS) extends his arm into Randle's (NYK) back and initiates contact that affects his ability to gain possession of the ball.
Williams (BOS) moves alongside Quickley's (NYK) path and avoids initiating illegal contact as he is contesting the driving shot attempt.
Barrett (NYK) places a collapsed forearm against Tatum's (BOS) side and incidental contact occurs as he releases away to contest the driving shot attempt.
Quickley (NYK) brings his off-arm toward Williams (BOS) and rests his hand on Williams' front during his drive toward the rim.
Robinson (NYK) attempts his free throw shot within ten seconds.
Tatum (BOS) reaches in and initiates contact with Robinson's (NYK) arm which affects his ability to move into his shot attempt.
Williams (BOS) firms up in Barrett's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.

Williams (BOS) reaches for the rebound and marginal contact occurs with Hart (NYK) as he returns to the floor.  Hart is not dislodged from his rebounding position as a result of the contact by Williams.
Randle (NYK) avoids making contact with Tatum (BOS) as he is contesting Tatum's driving shot attempt.
Horford (BOS) extends his arm into Robinson's (NYK) side and initiates contact that affects his ability to rebound the ball.
Horford (BOS) firms up in Hart's (NYK) path and incidental contact occurs as the pick is set.
Brown (BOS) doubles Quickley (NYK) in the post at the end of his drive and avoids making contact with his wrist.
Randle (NYK) does not get his shot off as the shot clock expires.
Hart (NYK) commits a personal take foul against Tatum (BOS).
Robinson (NYK) contests the jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Horford's (BOS) arm.
